# MongoDB Fundamentals Assignment

This repository contains the implementation of MongoDB fundamentals assignment focusing on CRUD operations, queries, aggregation pipelines, and indexing.

## Setup Instructions

1. Install Dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

2. MongoDB Setup:
   - Install MongoDB locally from [MongoDB Download Center](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community)
   - OR create a MongoDB Atlas account at [MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas/register)

3. Configure Environment:
   - Copy `.env` file and update the MongoDB connection URI if needed
   - Default configuration uses local MongoDB instance

4. Initialize Database:
```bash
npm run init-db
```

## Project Structure

- `src/config/db.js` - MongoDB connection configuration
- `src/insert_books.js` - Sample data insertion script
- `src/queries.js` - Your assignment queries implementation

## Running the Assignment Tasks

1. Initialize the database with sample data:
```bash
npm run init-db
```

2. Implement your queries in `src/queries.js`

3. Test your queries:
```bash
npm run test-queries
```

## Assignment Tasks

1. Basic CRUD Operations
   - Insert new books
   - Read books with various filters
   - Update book information
   - Delete books

2. Advanced Queries
   - Implement filtering
   - Use projections
   - Sort results
   - Use pagination

3. Aggregation Pipeline
   - Group books by genre
   - Calculate average prices
   - Find most popular authors

4. Indexing
   - Create appropriate indexes
   - Verify query performance improvements

